  "response": "Sumo wrestlers' weights can vary significantly, but on average, professional sumo wrestlers typically weigh between 300 to 400 pounds (136 to 181 kilograms). Some may weigh more, as the sport does not have a weight limit, and wrestlers often aim to be as large and powerful as possible within the bounds of their individual abilities and health considerations. The weight range can also depend on the division they wrestle in, with higher ranks potentially featuring larger wrestlers.",
